                            <comment id="13197338" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 31 Jan 2012 22:39:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So I&apos;m thinking: if the latest replacateable commit point is null and replicate on commit is on, we simply return the version/gen from the latest commit point.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13197350" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 31 Jan 2012 22:52:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;simple patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13197351" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 31 Jan 2012 22:53:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;there is a sys out in there ill cleanup&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13199501" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 3 Feb 2012 03:30:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This does not really solve things for the replicate on optimize option, but it does deal with the replicate on commit option and in general offers better behavior I think - I&apos;ll commit this soon if there is no objection.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
